    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/biotransformation-candidate-integration-with-networking/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "BAM leverages the principle that reactant and products of biochemical reactions often share molecular substructures, leading to high spectral similarity. This spectral similarity, when analyzed within a biological context, provides a more biologically relevant and comprehensive approach to annotation compared to traditional methods that rely solely on spectral similarity. BAM operates by identifying and applying biotransformation rules to an \"anchor\" molecule\u2014a known compound whose MS/MS spectrum exhibits high similarity to a given query spectrum.",
      "asbval:note": "Core research question is well-supported by the paper's description of BAM methodology.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-4c01565",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "biotransformation-candidate-integration-with-networking",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Integrates candidate structures predicted by biotransformation rules with untargeted MS/MS data via global molecular networking to construct a spectral similarity network and assign putative molecular structures to MS features.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T14:09:49.600979+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/biotransformation-candidate-integration-with-networking/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "As is standard methodology in molecular networking, the nodes of the global molecular network were annotated using standard spectral library searching against the default GNPS spectral libraries... From these nodes, we identified paired annotated compounds with high spectral similarity (modified cosine similarity above 0.8).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper uses molecular networking for spectral similarity clustering and structure prediction via biotransformation rules, but does not explicitly discuss 'network community membership' assignment as a primary output. The networking is used for anchor identification, not for community detection per se.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-4c01565",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "biotransformation-candidate-integration-with-networking",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This combines rule-based structure prediction with graph-based clustering to annotate metabolomics features with both predicted structures and network community membership.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T14:09:49.600979+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/biotransformation-candidate-integration-with-networking/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To extract and apply these rules, we employed PROXIMAL2. This tool aligns each reactant\u2013product pair using a maximum common substructure algorithm to identify the reaction center, and then creates a lookup table entry defining the changes at the reaction center and its neighbors... for a given anchor\u2013suspect pair, BAM applies the rules whose mass difference matches the observed precursor mass difference between the anchor and suspect to generate candidate derivatives for the query molecule.",
      "asbval:note": "PROXIMAL2 is confirmed as the tool for applying biotransformation rules to generate candidate structures.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-4c01565",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "biotransformation-candidate-integration-with-networking",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "PROXIMAL2 - Generates biotransformation rules and predicts candidate transformed structures for input to the networking step",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T14:09:49.600979+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/biotransformation-candidate-integration-with-networking/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Next, the graph neural network-based GNN-SOM tool is used to predict the site-of-metabolism and rank these putative derivatives based on the likelihood of each atom being a reaction center. GNN-SOM, a tool that employs a graph neural network to predict the likelihood of each atom in a molecule being the target of a biotransformation operation.",
      "asbval:note": "GNN-SOM is confirmed for site-of-metabolism prediction and ranking of candidate structures.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-4c01565",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "biotransformation-candidate-integration-with-networking",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "GNN-SOM - Performs site-of-metabolism prediction and ranking of enzymatic products to refine candidate structure generation",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T14:09:49.600979+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/biotransformation-candidate-integration-with-networking/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To address this problem, we have developed the Biotransformation-based Annotation Method (BAM). BAM consists of three steps (Figure 1): 1.For a given query spectrum, determine an annotated spectrum associated with an anchor molecule based on high spectral similarity. 2.Apply relevant biotransformation rules that match the observed mass difference between the anchor and suspect to generate candidate structures\u2014derivatives\u2014for the query spectrum. 3.Rank the derivatives based on the likelihoods of the applied biotransformation.",
      "asbval:note": "BAM is the orchestrating method that integrates biotransformation rules with molecular networking for annotation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-4c01565",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "biotransformation-candidate-integration-with-networking",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "BAM - Orchestrates the complete pipeline integrating biotransformation rules and global molecular networking",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T14:09:49.600979+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/biotransformation-candidate-integration-with-networking/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
