    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/smiles-parsing-validation/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "BAM operates by identifying and applying biotransformation rules to an 'anchor' molecule\u2014a known compound whose MS/MS spectrum exhibits high similarity to a given query spectrum. These rules, drawn from extensive biochemical databases like RetroRules and KEGG, encapsulate the promiscuous behavior of enzymes toward substrates.",
      "asbval:note": "BAM is confirmed as a biotransformation-based annotation pipeline for molecular structure discovery. However, the paper does not explicitly state that BAM requires validated SMILES as input; it describes BAM's workflow starting from anchor molecule identification based on spectral similarity, then applying biotransformation rules via PROXIMAL2. The input format and validation requirements are not detailed in the passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-4c01565",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "smiles-parsing-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools[HassounLab/BAM].role",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Biotransformation-based annotation pipeline that requires validated SMILES as input for molecular structure discovery",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T14:12:24.115096+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/smiles-parsing-validation/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "BAM leverages the principle that reactant and products of biochemical reactions often share molecular substructures, leading to high spectral similarity. This spectral similarity, when analyzed within a biological context, provides a more biologically relevant and comprehensive approach to annotation compared to traditional methods that rely solely on spectral similarity.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes BAM's application to untargeted metabolomics and biotransformation rule application, but does not explicitly frame SMILES parsing/validation as a prerequisite quality-control step. The paper focuses on the three-step BAM workflow (anchor identification, rule application via PROXIMAL2, ranking via GNN-SOM) rather than on input SMILES validation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-4c01565",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "smiles-parsing-validation",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Parse and validate SMILES strings using RDKit to ensure chemical validity before applying biotransformation rules or other molecular transformations. This is a prerequisite quality-control step for untargeted metabolomics workflows where input structures must be chemically sound.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T14:12:24.115096+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-similarity-network-construction/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Molecular networking uses spectral alignment via modified cosine similarity to visualize spectra and any corresponding annotations as a network, which enables additional interpretation of query spectra. The global molecular network was recently constructed from 521 million MS/MS spectra in 1335 public projects deposited to the GNPS/MassIVE... From these nodes, we identified paired annotated compounds with high spectral similarity (modified cosine similarity above 0.8).",
      "asbval:note": "Spectral similarity network construction via modified cosine similarity with filtering (>0.8 threshold) is explicitly described as the foundation for the BAM workflow.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-4c01565",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-similarity-network-construction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Construct a similarity network from untargeted metabolomics MS/MS spectral data by computing pairwise spectral similarity scores and filtering edges to retain high-confidence spectral matches.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T14:12:42.220089+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-similarity-network-construction/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "BAM operates by identifying and applying biotransformation rules to an 'anchor' molecule\u2014a known compound whose MS/MS spectrum exhibits high similarity to a given query spectrum... As a more efficient alternative, we utilized a precomputed molecular network, which we refer to as the global molecular network... we were able to obtain promising structural relationships efficiently.",
      "asbval:note": "The global molecular network (spectral similarity network) is explicitly used to identify anchor-suspect pairs and enable biotransformation-based annotation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-4c01565",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-similarity-network-construction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This network serves as the foundation for identifying molecular families and annotating candidate structures in metabolomic discovery workflows.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T14:12:42.220089+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-similarity-network-construction/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "For a given query spectrum, determine an annotated spectrum associated with an anchor molecule based on high spectral similarity... Apply relevant biotransformation rules that match the observed mass difference between the anchor and suspect to generate candidate structures.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes the workflow in reverse order: spectral similarity network construction (step 1) precedes biotransformation rule application (step 2), not after. The card's scope description inverts the actual workflow sequence.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-4c01565",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-similarity-network-construction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this skill after acquiring MS/MS spectral data from untargeted metabolomics experiments and having candidate transformed structures from biotransformation rule application.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T14:12:42.220089+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-similarity-network-construction/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To address this problem, we have developed the Biotransformation-based Annotation Method (BAM)... BAM consists of three steps (Figure 1): 1. For a given query spectrum, determine an annotated spectrum associated with an anchor molecule based on high spectral similarity... we utilized a precomputed molecular network, which we refer to as the global molecular network.",
      "asbval:note": "BAM explicitly uses global molecular networking (spectral similarity network) as step 1 of its three-step pipeline.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-4c01565",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-similarity-network-construction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "BAM orchestrates the complete biotransformation-based annotation pipeline, with spectral-similarity-network-construction as a core global molecular networking component",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T14:12:42.220089+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-similarity-network-construction/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To extract and apply these rules, we employed PROXIMAL2. This tool aligns each reactant\u2013product pair using a maximum common substructure algorithm to identify the reaction center... Finally, for a given anchor\u2013suspect pair, BAM applies the rules whose mass difference matches the observed precursor mass difference between the anchor and suspect to generate candidate derivatives for the query molecule.",
      "asbval:note": "PROXIMAL2 is used to apply biotransformation rules to generate candidate structures after anchor identification via the spectral similarity network.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-4c01565",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-similarity-network-construction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "PROXIMAL2 performs upstream biotransformation rule generation and candidate structure prediction feeding into network annotation",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T14:12:42.220089+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-similarity-network-construction/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Next, the graph neural network-based GNN-SOM tool is used to predict the site-of-metabolism and rank these putative derivatives based on the likelihood of each atom being a reaction center... For this, we use GNN-SOM, a tool that employs a graph neural network to predict the likelihood of each atom in a molecule being the target of a biotransformation operation.",
      "asbval:note": "GNN-SOM is used in step 3 of BAM to rank candidate structures generated from biotransformation rules applied to anchor molecules identified via the spectral similarity network.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-4c01565",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "spectral-similarity-network-construction",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "GNN-SOM performs graph neural network\u2013based site-of-metabolism prediction for ranking and refining candidate structures in the molecular network",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T14:12:42.220089+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
